parameters: Hey, we meet again, little lady.

What, you were worried about me? As expected of a champion
of justice, so kind-hearted.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]...Even if you're a bad person, I'd still feel bad waking up
to you dying right in front of me.

Hahaha! My durability is my best trait. I won't be biting
the dust that easily!
It was a bit scary though...
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]I have business further ahead, could you let me through?

I see, you want to assess our forces before the Guardians'
squad arrives, huh?
You think I'd just let you pass because you asked nicely?
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]Then, I'll just have to blast my way through... right.

Seriously... You're a feisty one, aren't you? There's
nothing more irresistible than breaking in a girl like that.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]I won't be broken... I won't lose to people who can only use
their power for such things!
Then show me that power of yours, magical girl!

Gah... not bad. So the power that defeated [Ogre] was the
real deal, huh...

Is this... what they call "power controlled within the
rules"...

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]It seems like you're misunderstanding something...
"Controlling power" doesn't mean to tie it down or anything
like that.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]It's about using your great power without causing trouble
for others, to make everyone happy, and to use that power
while abiding by the rules.

I like making weaklings grovel with this power, so I can't
accept what you're saying.

People who are aware that what they're doing is wrong by
societal standards won't be swayed by sound arguments,
right?

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]That's true... It might be difficult for everyone to
understand. But that doesn't mean what you guys did is
forgivable.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]It's fine to use your power however you like for yourself,
but you can't use it to take away "people's happiness"!

What you're saying might sound noble, but if you lose, you
can't say anything at all.

However, I've realized that the Guardians are tougher than I
expected. I'll have to warn Belial about this.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[0]Now that we've come this far, I want to go see for myself.
Of course, I'll be careful... okay!

I thought you'd say that... I'll support you as much as I
